                  <interp inst="t18050918-67-crimeloc352" type="placeName" value="Duke-street, Portland-place"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18050918-67-crimeloc352" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18050918-67-off350 t18050918-67-crimeloc352"></join>: On the 13th of August I came out of the cutting-room into the shop; we are <rs id="t18050918-67-viclabel353" type="occupation">tailors</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18050918-67-victim638 t18050918-67-viclabel353"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18050918-67-victim639 t18050918-67-viclabel353"></join>; I saw the prisoner with the articles under his arm; they were laying on the shelf in the shop; I had seen them about three minutes before.</p>
               <p>Q. Upon your coming out and seeing him, what did he do? - A. He immediately dropped them; I stopped him; he was rather impertinent, he asked me whether he had them in his hand, or under his arm; he said, that would make a great difference; I said I should leave it to a Justice to settle; while I went to get an officer, he made his escape; I ran after him when I came back, and took him; I am sure he is the same man.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I came in to buy an article that I had in my hand; I offered the prosecutor money for what I asked for.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18050918-67-verdict354" type="verdictDescription">
